All right, so way too late thoughts:

• Circle of Loyalty is definitely a cycle, right?
• I think I have... three different decks that Rankle slots right into?
• Adventure looks a lot cleaner on the commons and uncommons, and they're going to be houses in limited. I'm not sure I've seen any yet that are making a dent in EDH, however. Maybe the Gravedigger one in very specific decks, but that's about it and only because it flies.
• Garruk's "on each Garruk" wording and the Chandras from M20 really makes me think that Wizards has heard the call for things like "Oops, All Gideons" and is leaning into it fairly hard.
• Midnight Clock is a bad mana rock with an excellent upside. If it stays cheap, it should see play in all sorts of both niche and budget decks.
• I'm... tentatively excited about food, but do feel that the artifact type makes them clunky flavor-wise. Enchantment would have made more sense mechanically, but still isn't a hit flavor-wise... I'm not sure anything short of a new permanent type would have been, so all in all I guess this is fine? I dunno.
• Syr Konrad already has me thinking brewing thoughts.
• Throne of Eldraine is the time to launch Joust. *KNIGHTS!*

I guess I should put it this way - Commander precons used to be one of the only places where we received interesting new legends. They're not that anymore; as the popularity of the format increased, other sets included spicier legends to meet that demand.

What that's caused, though, is the Commander precons to feel like they're not anything inherently more special than the regular sets. They need something else, some extra oomph. I'm not convinced c19 had that oomph. I'm actually pretty sure 19 was one of my least favorite Commander products, beaten out only by c13. I didn't like the new commanders, I didn't like the new cards in the 99, I didn't like the reprints, and I utterly loathed the gameplay. All it takes is one of those pillars to be good and I love the product - that's why I actually like c18, it had cool commanders even though the other categories kinda blew - but c19 was missing on all accounts.

And now it's being drowned out by other products. It needs something else to stand out because otherwise it's an indistinct product. It needs a new oomph.
